from a scientific approach,

00:04:35.460 --> 00:04:40.110 align:middle line:84%
that our experiential world
represents just a small thread

00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:44.700 align:middle line:84%
in a much larger tapestry of
wholeness and completeness.

00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:49.110 align:middle line:84%
Pauli and Jung believed that
higher dimensional tapestry

00:04:49.110 --> 00:04:52.050 align:middle line:84%
to be a metaphysical
reality, one

00:04:52.050 --> 00:04:56.370 align:middle line:84%
that is home to the collective
unconscious and the archetypes.

00:04:56.370 --> 00:04:59.740 align:middle line:84%
What is meant by
collective unconscious?

00:04:59.740 --> 00:05:04.140 align:middle line:84%
Jung defined it as a collective,
universal, and impersonal

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:08.130 align:middle line:84%
nature which is identical
in all individuals.

00:05:08.130 --> 00:05:11.130 align:middle line:84%
This collective
unconscious is inherited.

00:05:11.130 --> 00:05:16.260 align:middle line:84%
And it consists of pre-existent
forms, the archetypes.

00:05:16.260 --> 00:05:19.050 align:middle line:84%
He saw it as a
timeless realm out

00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:21.630 align:middle line:90%
of which consciousness evolves.

00:05:21.630 --> 00:05:24.840 align:middle line:84%
Jung's research revealed
that symbols, dreams,

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:27.630 align:middle line:84%
synchronicities,
