marriage of matter and psyche,

00:08:57.380 --> 00:08:59.900 align:middle line:90%
of physical and spiritual.

00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:03.950 align:middle line:84%
Let's imagine for a moment
that the horizontal axis

00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:07.670 align:middle line:84%
represents our entire
three-dimensional physical

00:09:07.670 --> 00:09:08.870 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:09:08.870 --> 00:09:12.080 align:middle line:84%
As we can see, it
cuts a single line

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:14.600 align:middle line:90%
through this complex plane.

00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:17.210 align:middle line:90%
It is but a slice.

00:09:17.210 --> 00:09:20.780 align:middle line:84%
Likewise, if we imagine
that the vertical axis

00:09:20.780 --> 00:09:23.330 align:middle line:84%
of the imaginary
numbers represents

00:09:23.330 --> 00:09:27.830 align:middle line:84%
the world of pure spirit,
we can see that on its own,

00:09:27.830 --> 00:09:30.440 align:middle line:90%
it too, is just a slice.

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:34.850 align:middle line:84%
But together, they create a
rich field of possibility.

00:09:34.850 --> 00:09:37.610 align:middle line:84%
And this might be
why spirit has chosen

00:09:37.610 --> 00:09:40.040 align:middle line:84%
to come into the
physical, to give us

00:09:40.040 --> 00:09:44.620 align:middle line:84%
more possibilities for
experience and growth.

00:09:44.620 --> 00:09:46.870 align:middle line:84%
Only by expanding
our consciousness

00:09:46.870 --> 00:09:50.140 align:middle line:84%
beyond the physical can
we bring our awareness

00:09:50.140 --> 00:09:53.680 align:middle line:84%
to greatness and pierce
the veils of illusion.

00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:57.940 align:middle line:84%
This means we need to lift off
that horizontal axis, where

00:09:57.940 --> 00:10:00.670 align:middle line:84%
we get focused on just
the physical realm,

00:10:00.670 --> 00:10:04.330 align:middle line:84%
and gain some higher perspective
from the non-physical planes

00:10:04.330 --> 00:10:07.120 align:middle line:90%
of the vertical axis.

00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:09.610 align:middle line:84%
Of course, we've heard
this idea before.

00:10:09.610 --> 00:10:13.510 align:middle line:84%
But by now associating this
concept with the i ring,

00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:16.510 align:middle line:90%
it reveals even deeper insights.

00:10:16.510 --> 00:10:17.920 align:middle line:90%
Like what?

00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:20.950 align:middle line:84%
Well, first, this brings
us back to the idea

00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:25.600 align:middle line:84%
of hado, or vibrational essence,
discussed in other episodes.

00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:29.380 align:middle line:84%
Recall that Dr. Masaru Emoto is
very dedicated to the science

00:10:29.380 --> 00:10:32.020 align:middle line:90%
of hado and its applications.

00:10:32.020 --> 00:10:35.920 align:middle line:84%
Hado is that vibrational
energy of atomic waves

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:38.470 align:middle line:84%
generated by the
dynamic movements

00:10:38.470 --> 00:10:43.060 align:middle line:84%
of the electrons, quarks, and
central fire within atoms.

00:10:43.060 --> 00:10:45.700 align:middle line:84%
In his book "Truth
of Hado," Dr. Emoto

00:10:45.700 --> 00:10:49.780 align:middle line:84%
cites another eminent Japanese
scientist, Dr. Ohashi,

00:10:49.780 --> 00:10:53.590 align:middle line:84%
who researched extensively
into the science of hado.

00:10:53.590 --> 00:10:56.170 align:middle line:84%
In one of his books
on hado science,

00:10:56.170 --> 00:11:01.090 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Ohashi introduces the
concept of imaginary nature.

00:11:01.090 --> 00:11:03.910 align:middle line:84%
In ancient Japanese
kanji, this concept

00:11:03.910 --> 00:11:07.510 align:middle line:84%
is known as kyoshitsu,
which can also be

00:11:07.510 --> 00:11:10.240 align:middle line:90%
translated as void substance.

00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Kyo in kanji means emptiness,
void, or imaginary.

00:11:14.860 --> 00:11:19.360 align:middle line:84%
Shitsu means nature,
quality, or substance.

00:11:19.360 --> 00:11:23.110 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Ohashi explained
that imaginary nature

00:11:23.110 --> 00:11:29.230 align:middle line:84%
is analogous to emptiness in
Buddhism or hollow in Daoism,

00:11:29.230 --> 00:11:33.700 align:middle line:84%
one body in Western philosophy,
or the sacred, essential hoa

00:11:33.700 --> 00:11:35.080 align:middle line:90%
in kabbalah.

00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:39.340 align:middle line:84%
Hoa in Hebrew means he,
himself, or in Aramaic, it

00:11:39.340 --> 00:11:41.980 align:middle line:90%
means fulfilled or to exist.

00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:48.790 align:middle line:84%
Scientifically, this all relates
to the quantum vacuum or ether.

00:11:48.790 --> 00:11:52.070 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Ohashi she goes on
to say that the concept

00:11:52.070 --> 00:11:56.030 align:middle line:84%
of imaginary nature is
the basis of hado science.

00:11:56.030 --> 00:11:58.550 align:middle line:84%
If the ocean is
the mother of life,

00:11:58.550 --> 00:12:03.510 align:middle line:84%
then imaginary nature is
the parent of the universe.

00:12:03.510 --> 00:12:07.400 align:middle line:84%
This is, again, very similar
to David Bohm's description

00:12:07.400 --> 00:12:10.210 align:middle line:90%
of the implicate order.

00:12:10.210 --> 00:12:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Ohashi uses the
terms real dimensions

00:12:12.860 --> 00:12:15.920 align:middle line:84%
to represent this 3D
physical world which

00:12:15.920 --> 00:12:17.960 align:middle line:90%
